WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:09.810 --> 00:00:12.473
Okay. this is insane.

2
00:00:12.546 --> 00:00:15.641
- We need more Compound V!
- Absolutely.

3
00:00:15.716 --> 00:00:17.048
We need more Supes!

4
00:00:17.150 --> 00:00:22.214
<i>More Supes! More Supes! More Supes!</i>

5
00:00:22.322 --> 00:00:23.322
Come with me.

6
00:00:24.391 --> 00:00:25.689
What are you doing here?

7
00:00:27.294 --> 00:00:31.163
I'm sleeping in a basement
beneath a pawn shop in East Flatbush.

8
00:00:31.231 --> 00:00:32.597
I never wanted that for you.

9
00:00:32.699 --> 00:00:34.677
[Homelander] We have
Ryan's best interests at heart.

10
00:00:34.701 --> 00:00:37.296
- I want us to be a family.
- They flew me up and showed me!

11
00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:39.397
This house. the neighbors are fake.
You're fake.

12
00:00:39.506 --> 00:00:41.338
No! Ryan!

13
00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:43.502
You have five minutes
to make your opening...

14
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:51.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

15
00:00:57.891 --> 00:00:59.931
[man] There's a super villain
on your school campus.

16
00:01:00.027 --> 00:01:01.859
You hear the calls of distress.

17
00:01:01.929 --> 00:01:04.023
You witness a violent display
of superpowers.

18
00:01:04.097 --> 00:01:05.190
What do you do?

19
00:01:05.265 --> 00:01:06.858
I'm Sheriff Ed Flanagan.

20
00:01:06.934 --> 00:01:09.927
and I'm here with Homelander
to talk about school safety.

21
00:01:10.037 --> 00:01:12.438
On the first report
of an active super villain.

22
00:01:12.539 --> 00:01:14.770
a hero will immediately
rush to your campus.

23
00:01:14.875 --> 00:01:16.969
But to stay alive in the moment.
remember.

24
00:01:17.611 --> 00:01:20.080
stay calm and follow the LAW.

25
00:01:21.048 --> 00:01:23.040
Lock all doors and windows.

26
00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:27.744
Arm yourselves.

27
00:01:27.854 --> 00:01:30.449
Your teacher should have
an authorized firearm.

28
00:01:34.127 --> 00:01:35.652
But use whatever you can.

29
00:01:38.398 --> 00:01:40.162
And wait for a hero.

30
00:01:43.003 --> 00:01:44.437
[woman screaming]

31
00:01:44.504 --> 00:01:46.302
[Ed]
Unfortunately. the possibility that...

32
00:01:46.406 --> 00:01:48.238
you will experience
a super villain attack

33
00:01:48.308 --> 00:01:49.776
grows more likely every day.

34
00:01:49.876 --> 00:01:51.310
By having an action plan.

35
00:01:51.411 --> 00:01:53.812
you can increase your chances
of survival.

36
00:01:53.914 --> 00:01:56.383
And survival is all that matters.

37
00:01:58.518 --> 00:02:02.182
- [reporter] <i>Coverage of the attack...</i>
- Jody! Where's my flag pin?

38
00:02:02.289 --> 00:02:03.484
[Jody] How should I know?

39
00:02:03.590 --> 00:02:05.889
Well. I can't go to this thing
without a flag pin.

40
00:02:05.959 --> 00:02:08.895
Bob. before he makes any decisions.
just let me talk to him.

41
00:02:08.962 --> 00:02:13.161
One. the president doesn't like you.
he used the word "standoffish."

42
00:02:13.266 --> 00:02:15.258
And two. he's decided.

43
00:02:15.335 --> 00:02:18.635
He's declaring a national emergency.
bypassing the FDA.

44
00:02:18.705 --> 00:02:20.503
and authorizing Compound V for use...

45
00:02:20.607 --> 00:02:22.667
by law enforcement
and first responders.

46
00:02:22.776 --> 00:02:25.541
- Are you fucking kidding me?
- I wish I were.

47
00:02:25.646 --> 00:02:27.808
Doses are going for 5 million a pop.

48
00:02:27.914 --> 00:02:31.442
Pentagon's got a big order in.
and ICE is next in line.

49
00:02:31.518 --> 00:02:33.487
You can't release V
into the mainstream.

50
00:02:33.553 --> 00:02:35.317
we're talking an avalanche of Supes.

51
00:02:35.422 --> 00:02:36.422
It's suicide.

52
00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:37.355
In one hour.

53
00:02:37.457 --> 00:02:39.289
I will be standing
at the memorial service

54
00:02:39.359 --> 00:02:41.419
for the fallen heroes
of the House attack.

55
00:02:41.495 --> 00:02:42.963
with my flag pin!

56
00:02:43.030 --> 00:02:47.627
Giving my thoughts and prayers
and pledging to keep America safe.

57
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:50.069
The best way to do that
is with Compound V.

58
00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:51.890
[Victoria]
We know. We were there. remember?

59
00:02:51.938 --> 00:02:55.932
Covered in my chief of staff's brains.
There was no terrorist. it was Vought.

60
00:02:56.009 --> 00:02:57.978
It's a fucking coup.

61
00:02:58.045 --> 00:03:01.140
- A bunch of their guys died too.
- To cover their own tracks.

62
00:03:02.883 --> 00:03:06.581
For the record. I agree with you.
And I hate this.

63
00:03:06.687 --> 00:03:08.952
But you've got no proof.

64
00:03:09.022 --> 00:03:10.854
Folks are scared.

65
00:03:10.957 --> 00:03:13.153
If Vought took a shit
in the middle of Fifth Avenue.

66
00:03:13.226 --> 00:03:14.888
they'd throw a ticker tape parade.

67
00:03:14.995 --> 00:03:17.988
- Here's what we do have. Bob...
- Oh. let me guess.

68
00:03:18.065 --> 00:03:21.263
A tape of me fucking my kid's nanny
at her daughter's quinceañera?

69
00:03:21.368 --> 00:03:24.395
Release it. please. I'm begging you.

70
00:03:24.504 --> 00:03:27.997
A plumb gig at Fox
and this shithole in my rear-view?

71
00:03:28.075 --> 00:03:29.075
Sounds dreamy.

72
00:03:29.109 --> 00:03:32.204
Okay. what if we got hard proof?
A witness? Anything?

73
00:03:32.279 --> 00:03:34.544
[Bob] If you could get
Jesus Christ himself.

74
00:03:34.614 --> 00:03:37.675
or maybe Homelander
in front of a camera. sure.

75
00:03:38.485 --> 00:03:39.748
I really am sorry.

76
00:03:42.222 --> 00:03:43.520
[dogs barking]

77
00:04:16.423 --> 00:04:18.517
[Donna] I'm nervous
about driving in the city.

78
00:04:18.592 --> 00:04:20.584
You'll be okay. The plan again?

79
00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:23.289
Okay.
drive straight to Gen's in Sedona.

80
00:04:23.396 --> 00:04:25.228
Cash for gasoline. no hotels.

81
00:04:26.967 --> 00:04:29.596
- I don't wanna leave you here.
- I'll be fine.

82
00:04:33.907 --> 00:04:36.638
The anxious boy? Really?
With the moist handshake?

83
00:04:36.743 --> 00:04:39.178
- Mom! God.
- Okay. All right. okay.

84
00:04:39.279 --> 00:04:40.279
Um.

85
00:04:40.647 --> 00:04:42.081
You need a new one.

86
00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:44.450
I...

87
00:04:46.319 --> 00:04:47.685
I'm not gonna wear it.

88
00:04:48.688 --> 00:04:51.487
I don't care if you wear it.
I just want you to have it.

89
00:04:56.062 --> 00:04:57.189
I love you.

90
00:04:57.697 --> 00:04:58.995
I love you too.

91
00:05:01.935 --> 00:05:03.130
You be safe.

92
00:05:03.203 --> 00:05:04.501
- Okay.
- Bye.

93
00:05:08.341 --> 00:05:09.434
Hey.

94
00:05:10.177 --> 00:05:12.009
- What's going on?
- They've lost their minds.

95
00:05:12.112 --> 00:05:15.571
The RPG releases
an electromagnetic pulse on impact.

96
00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:18.182
Should cut through
Stormfront's plasma bolts.

97
00:05:18.285 --> 00:05:20.220
- How sure are you?
- It's a guesstimate.

98
00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:21.948
So that's Stormfront.

99
00:05:22.689 --> 00:05:25.989
And thanks to Starlight. we know
that Noir needs any fucking tree nut.

100
00:05:26.092 --> 00:05:27.092
How about A-Train?

101
00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:29.595
Enough epinephrine
to blow up that motherfucker's heart.

102
00:05:29.663 --> 00:05:33.532
- Hey. we can't just kill everyone.
- That is exactly what we're gonna do.

103
00:05:33.633 --> 00:05:34.692
Listen. you heard Mallory.

104
00:05:34.801 --> 00:05:36.394
she said
all we need is another witness.

105
00:05:36.503 --> 00:05:38.028
Wile E. Coyote.

106
00:05:39.673 --> 00:05:41.107
Always chases Road Runner.

107
00:05:41.174 --> 00:05:43.803
Always with an elaborate plan.
Always fails.

108
00:05:43.877 --> 00:05:46.210
I always say. why do this. Coyote?

109
00:05:46.313 --> 00:05:49.841
All you need is an AR-15
and "meep-meep." no more.

110
00:05:50.684 --> 00:05:53.813
Exactly. See? We're just gonna shoot
Road Runner in the fucking head.

111
00:05:53.887 --> 00:05:57.119
That won't stop Vought.
That won't stop Compound V.

112
00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:59.887
If you kill these Supes.
Vought will just make a thousand more.

113
00:05:59.993 --> 00:06:02.485
- I'm gonna top those cunts too.
- [grunts]

114
00:06:02.562 --> 00:06:03.689
Great. So that's settled.

115
00:06:03.763 --> 00:06:07.632
- We're just super villains now. huh?
- Vought attacked the country. Hughie.

116
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:08.896
Fuck them all.

117
00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:13.139
What if I testify?

118
00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:15.698
Escaped convicts
don't have a ton of credibility.

119
00:06:17.077 --> 00:06:20.514
No.
but maybe I know someone who does.

120
00:06:21.915 --> 00:06:23.349
Give us the day.

121
00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:25.551
Hughie.

122
00:06:27.153 --> 00:06:28.153
See you later.

123
00:06:28.788 --> 00:06:32.782
<i>Officials are still trying to determine
the perpetrator of the Capitol attack.</i>

124
00:06:32.893 --> 00:06:37.422
<i>The Department of Homeland Security
has issued a crimson terror alert.</i>

125
00:06:37.931 --> 00:06:39.900
<i>In Washington.
all government buildings...</i>

126
00:06:39.966 --> 00:06:42.526
- How's Noir?
- Unresponsive.

127
00:06:42.602 --> 00:06:46.437
They don't think there's brain damage.
but it's hard to tell.

128
00:06:46.539 --> 00:06:49.771
Noir's a vegetable.
Lamplighter's a charcoal briquette.

129
00:06:49.876 --> 00:06:52.869
Starlight's in the breeze somewhere.
And you're. what. fine with it?

130
00:06:52.946 --> 00:06:54.710
Yes.
because none of that matters anymore.

131
00:06:54.781 --> 00:06:55.781
Because of this.

132
00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:59.716
<i>So far. no terrorist group
has claimed responsibility...</i>

133
00:06:59.786 --> 00:07:03.985
- All right. So. you didn't do this.
- I wish I'd killed Vogelbaum.

134
00:07:04.925 --> 00:07:06.917
- But. no. it wasn't me.
- Right.

135
00:07:06.993 --> 00:07:09.792
And there's no super villains
on American soil.

136
00:07:09.896 --> 00:07:12.297
- None that we know of.
- Then that means...

137
00:07:14.701 --> 00:07:15.828
It's Edgar.

138
00:07:16.603 --> 00:07:20.005
Maybe. I mean. he is pretty smart.
especially for his kind.

139
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:23.270
<i>Compound V to members of the
military and law enforcement...</i>

140
00:07:23.343 --> 00:07:27.280
Hey. smile. This is good news.

141
00:07:28.315 --> 00:07:30.284
Yes. there have been sacrifices.

142
00:07:30.350 --> 00:07:35.152
but we are this close
to no more premieres or paparazzi.

143
00:07:35.255 --> 00:07:38.657
Or screaming fans
or any of that dancing-monkey shit.

144
00:07:39.726 --> 00:07:42.093
We have to make sure that
the right people get the doses.

145
00:07:42.162 --> 00:07:44.131
but it is a whole new world.

146
00:07:45.498 --> 00:07:47.296
What about the wrong people?

147
00:07:47.367 --> 00:07:50.929
Couple of billion of them.
they're not just gonna sit there.

148
00:07:51.671 --> 00:07:53.037
Don't worry. silly.

149
00:07:53.139 --> 00:07:55.973
Frederick
had a solution for everything.

150
00:08:02.248 --> 00:08:04.547
Okay.
There's something really important...

151
00:08:04.651 --> 00:08:06.620
that I've been meaning to ask you.

152
00:08:07.754 --> 00:08:10.349
Last I checked. you're not 57 years old.

153
00:08:10.457 --> 00:08:15.259
So. come on.
why is it always. always Billy Joel?

154
00:08:15.328 --> 00:08:18.765
- I'm 57 on the inside.
- No. really. Please.

155
00:08:20.667 --> 00:08:22.898
It was just the music
in my house growing up.

156
00:08:23.003 --> 00:08:25.268
I did some somersaults
to "You May Be Right"

157
00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:27.500
that were pretty thrilling to watch.

158
00:08:28.408 --> 00:08:32.709
<i>♪ Only the good die young
That's what I'm saying... ♪</i>

159
00:08:32.812 --> 00:08:35.145
Butcher is right. you know.

160
00:08:35.782 --> 00:08:38.479
We've already tried
to take Vought down the right way.

161
00:08:38.551 --> 00:08:39.712
This isn't gonna work.

162
00:08:39.819 --> 00:08:42.584
This is not gonna stop Compound V
from getting out there.

163
00:08:42.689 --> 00:08:43.816
So it's hopeless?

164
00:08:43.890 --> 00:08:46.883
Just kill them all.
let God sort them out?

165
00:08:46.993 --> 00:08:47.993
I mean...

166
00:08:50.597 --> 00:08:52.691
Then why are you even helping me?

167
00:08:54.601 --> 00:08:56.399
Why did you save me at the Tower?

168
00:08:56.503 --> 00:08:58.404
They were gonna hurt you.

169
00:08:58.505 --> 00:09:00.667
You could've gotten yourself killed.

170
00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:05.838
I mean. after the way that I treated you.
you had every reason to give up on me.

171
00:09:05.912 --> 00:09:07.380
So why didn't you?

172
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:13.919
I just... would never.

173
00:09:16.256 --> 00:09:17.690
That's why I'm helping.

174
00:09:27.834 --> 00:09:29.200
[Maeve sighs]

175
00:09:30.136 --> 00:09:31.900
You were stupid to text.

176
00:09:34.040 --> 00:09:35.702
Everyone's looking for you.

177
00:09:36.643 --> 00:09:37.872
Where's Elena?

178
00:09:39.546 --> 00:09:40.980
This is the guy?

179
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:43.277
Um...

180
00:09:43.383 --> 00:09:46.649
I'm... Hi. Hughie.

181
00:09:47.754 --> 00:09:49.985
He's even more of a twink
than in the photo.

182
00:09:51.357 --> 00:09:53.952
I could split that shit like dry firewood.

183
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:56.595
Big fan.

184
00:09:57.497 --> 00:09:58.795
I need to ask you something.

185
00:10:00.366 --> 00:10:01.390
It's a lot.

186
00:10:02.936 --> 00:10:06.429
- I need you to testify.
- Testify?

187
00:10:06.506 --> 00:10:07.872
On the record.

188
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:13.171
Against Vought. against Homelander.
Stormfront. everything.

189
00:10:14.147 --> 00:10:19.108
- And why would I do that?
- Because things are really bad. and...

190
00:10:21.187 --> 00:10:22.314
you're our last chance.

191
00:10:22.422 --> 00:10:23.446
Pass.

192
00:10:23.523 --> 00:10:26.891
- Look. I get that it's dangerous.
- It's suicide.

193
00:10:27.894 --> 00:10:30.125
- But that's not the reason.
- Well. then what is?

194
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:32.822
I'm tired.

195
00:10:34.134 --> 00:10:38.037
We're all tired.
but they're hurting people.

196
00:10:38.771 --> 00:10:40.706
Sooner or later.
they'll hurt someone you love.

197
00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:41.807
Am I talking to you?

198
00:10:43.143 --> 00:10:44.668
[Annie] Look...

199
00:10:48.114 --> 00:10:55.112
I get that it's easier
to just disappear inside of yourself.

200
00:10:55.188 --> 00:10:57.214
Trust me. it's all I want to do.

201
00:10:57.323 --> 00:10:59.019
But we can't. Maeve.

202
00:11:00.126 --> 00:11:01.492
We can't.

203
00:11:02.195 --> 00:11:05.791
- This is a war now. and we...
- Shut the fuck up.

204
00:11:05.865 --> 00:11:07.424
Christ. you...

205
00:11:07.934 --> 00:11:09.835
Haven't I done enough for you?

206
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:16.207
Didn't I save your fucking life?

207
00:11:19.012 --> 00:11:22.244
It doesn't matter what we do.
Nothing changes.

208
00:11:27.554 --> 00:11:31.457
Nothing ever changes or gets better.

209
00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:37.724
And I'm tired.

210
00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:41.827
Just leave.

211
00:11:43.570 --> 00:11:44.570
Go!

212
00:11:45.471 --> 00:11:48.566
Take your fucking twink
and get the fuck out of here!

213
00:11:49.709 --> 00:11:50.709
Okay.

214
00:11:51.911 --> 00:11:53.004
Come on.

215
00:12:08.595 --> 00:12:11.258
Monsieur Charcuterie.
we need you. Now.

216
00:12:14.133 --> 00:12:16.932
[Becca] He said he lives under
a pawn shop in East Flatbush!

217
00:12:17.036 --> 00:12:19.801
- He has to be here! Help me.
- Let her in.

218
00:12:20.807 --> 00:12:24.209
Billy. They took him.

219
00:12:24.944 --> 00:12:26.879
- They have Ryan.
- Who's got him?

220
00:12:31.751 --> 00:12:33.811
I appreciate you
coming all this way. Stan.

221
00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:39.085
Well. I can't exactly be seen
with you at the Tower now. can I?

222
00:12:39.726 --> 00:12:42.924
- Fresca?
- No. thank you. Awful stuff.

223
00:12:45.265 --> 00:12:48.292
So you had a chance
to look over our proposal?

224
00:12:48.401 --> 00:12:51.394
He publicly confessed
to a sexual assault. Alastair.

225
00:12:51.471 --> 00:12:54.669
And we've made a substantial
investment in the Deep's rehabilitation.

226
00:12:54.774 --> 00:12:58.734
Our internal research bureau
shows an impressive Q rating.

227
00:12:58.811 --> 00:13:03.078
He's an asset to Vought
in these troubled times.

228
00:13:03.149 --> 00:13:06.813
Oh. what sort of commission
is the church getting these days?

229
00:13:06.919 --> 00:13:08.683
Forty percent? 50?

230
00:13:08.788 --> 00:13:11.280
Sounds like you're open
to reinstatement.

231
00:13:11.357 --> 00:13:12.357
That's fantastic.

232
00:13:14.160 --> 00:13:15.856
What about A-Train?

233
00:13:15.962 --> 00:13:18.488
You do need a speedster
since Shockwave exploded.

234
00:13:18.598 --> 00:13:23.093
Harder sell.
One has-been back is redemption.

235
00:13:23.169 --> 00:13:24.865
Two is weakness.

236
00:13:25.505 --> 00:13:27.064
Stormfront has problems with him.

237
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:29.632
And at the moment.
I have to indulge her.

238
00:13:30.777 --> 00:13:32.678
What's her problem with A-Train?

239
00:13:33.680 --> 00:13:37.879
I understand that she was among
your grandfather's first followers.

240
00:13:37.984 --> 00:13:40.385
back when
the Collective was a start-up.

241
00:13:42.355 --> 00:13:44.449
I can neither confirm or deny that.

242
00:13:44.524 --> 00:13:45.958
[chuckles]

243
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:50.994
Then your internal research bureau
knows exactly

244
00:13:51.097 --> 00:13:53.589
what Stormfront's problem is
with A-Train.

245
00:13:55.201 --> 00:13:56.897
Deep is still a win.

246
00:13:57.470 --> 00:13:59.166
Shall I have Business Affairs
